heavily /ˈhɛvɪlɪ/

ADV If someone says something heavily , they say it in a slow way which shows a feeling such as sadness, tiredness, or annoyance. 缓慢沉痛地; 沉重地 [ADV after v]  →  see also heavy 

例： 'I didn't even think about her,' he said heavily. “我根本都没想到过她，”他沉重地说道。

